data.title: 以至少 50 个字回答问题
data.content: "Describe an important place (such as a business or a meeting place) in the city or town where you live. What is it? Why is it important? Give a few reasons."
data.answer: I currently live in Sydney, and there is a very famous place called Town Hall. Town Hall is located in the city center, between the city shopping and entertainment precincts. The Sydney Town Hall is a late 19th-century heritage-listed town hall building in the city of Sydney, the capital city of New South Wales, Australia, housing the chambers of the Lord Mayor of Sydney, council offices, and venues for meetings and functions. It is also a landmark for Sydney as it is close to the Queen Victoria Building. All tourists to Sydney would visit this place to see its historical architectural style. (102 words)
